Date: Mon 28 Mar 2005
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Xinhua News Agency online, Mon 28 Mar 2005 [edited]
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-03/28/content_2752538.htm>

Viet Nam: new suspected case of avian influenza virus infection
-----------------------------------------------
A 41-year-old woman from Viet Nam's northern city of Hai Phong has been
hospitalized on suspicion of having contracted avian influenza A (H5N1)
virus. The woman, who resides in the Kien Thuy district, was admitted to a
hospital in the city on 25 Mar 2005 after suffering cough and breathing
difficulty, according to the newspaper Youth on Mon 28 Mar 2005. She lives
in an avian influenza-affected area near a 5-person family admitted to the
city-based Viet-Tiep Hospital on 22 Mar 2005 with avian influenza symptoms.
Specimens from the family members are being tested for the presence of the
H5N1 virus. The Vietnamese Health Ministry has just confirmed that 28 local
people have been infected with H5N1 since 26 Dec 2004, of whom 14 died.
To prevent spread of H5N1 virus among fowl, and from poultry to people, the
Ministry has urged all cities and provinces nationwide to intensify
disinfection of their poultry facilities. A nationwide hygiene campaign
will be conducted for one month starting on Fri 1 Apr 2005. Avian influenza
has stricken a total of 35 cities and provinces in Viet Nam since January
2005. Of these, 26 localities have detected no new affected spots for 5
weeks as of 26 Mar 2005, meeting requirements for declaration of an end to
the [outbreak]. Of the remaining 9 localities, 7 localities are in the
southern region, and 2 in the northern region.
